The article is a transcript of a press briefing about Vice President Biden's upcoming trip to Southern Europe in 2009. The trip includes visits to Bosnia-Herzegovina, Serbia, and Kosovo. In Bosnia-Herzegovina, Biden plans to show support for Dayton, Bosnian sovereignty, and state-building reforms. In Serbia, he hopes to improve relations and emphasize Serbia's role in the region. In Kosovo, Biden will emphasize support for a unified, independent, and multiethnic Kosovo. The trip signifies a refocus on the Balkans and a desire to strengthen US engagement in the region.